abbr: Windows Management Instrumentation

«Instrumentation» because it shows internal values of windows like dashboard instruments in a car do.

WMI is → Microsoft/index[Microsoft's] implementation of → development/misc/WBEM and → development/misc/CIF.

{ WMI Objects

  Win32_Process, Win32_Service, AntiVirusProduct, Win32_Startup ...

  WMI objects are queried using a → development/databases/SQL like language: *WMI Query Language (WQL)*.

  Persistent objects are stored in `%→development/environment-variable#systemroot[SystemRoot]%\System32\wbem\Repository\OBJECTS.DATA`. 

}

{ winmgmt

  ? The WMI service.

}
